                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 10.792,
                                "byte_start": 87617,
                                "byte_stop": 130876,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court No. 00-1072, Edelman against Lynchburg College will be announced by Justice Souter."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 10.792,
                        "stop": 249.077,
                        "byte_start": 130876,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15042,
                            "name": "David H. Souter",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/david_h_souter",
                            "last_name": "Souter",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2686,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 655362000,
                                    "date_end": 1246251600,
                                    "appointing_president": "George H. W. Bush",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2686"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32703,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 42141,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/david_souter.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 6839,
                            "identifier": "david_h_souter"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 10.792,
                                "stop": 16.443,
                                "byte_start": 130876,
                                "byte_stop": 153446,
                                "text": "This case comes to us on writ of certiorari of the Court of Appeals for the Fourth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 16.443,
                                "stop": 33.51,
                                "byte_start": 153446,
                                "byte_stop": 221677,
                                "text": "In November of 1997, the petitioner Leonard Edelman faxed a letter to the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission alleging that the Respondent, Lynchburg College had discriminated against him on the basis of gender, national origin, and religion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 33.51,
                                "stop": 54.322,
                                "byte_start": 221677,
                                "byte_stop": 304956,
                                "text": "The letter was not signed under oath and it was only after the statutory 300-day period for filing complaints under Title VII of the Civil Rights Act that Edelman sent the EEOC one of its Forms No. 5 charging discrimination verified under oath."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.322,
                                "stop": 59.216,
                                "byte_start": 304956,
                                "byte_stop": 324495,
                                "text": "The EEOC investigated the claim and issued Edelman a right to sue letter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 59.216,
                                "stop": 69.893,
                                "byte_start": 324495,
                                "byte_stop": 367232,
                                "text": "Edelman filed an action in State Court which the college moved to the Federal Court after Edelman amended his complaint to a certain cause of action under Title VII."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.893,
                                "stop": 79.136,
                                "byte_start": 367232,
                                "byte_stop": 404221,
                                "text": "The College then filed a motion to dismiss the action because Edelman had not filed the charge with the EEOC within the 300-day period."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 79.136,
                                "stop": 93.62,
                                "byte_start": 404221,
                                "byte_stop": 462108,
                                "text": "The District Court granted the motion to dismiss finding that Edelman\u2019s unsworn November 1997 letter was not intended to bay nor was it treated as a charge within the meaning of Title VII."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 93.62,
                                "stop": 113.409,
                                "byte_start": 462108,
                                "byte_stop": 541312,
                                "text": "The District Court did not passed on Edelman\u2019s argument that his November 1997 letter was a timely charge file that even without an oath and that under the EEOC regulations the oath verifying the Form 5 related back to the original letter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 113.409,
                                "stop": 116.685,
                                "byte_start": 541312,
                                "byte_stop": 554373,
                                "text": "A divided panel of the Court of Appeals affirmed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 116.685,
                                "stop": 127.643,
                                "byte_start": 554373,
                                "byte_stop": 598259,
                                "text": "The majority held that Edelman had not filed with the EEOC in time because the letter he filed within the 300-day period was not signed under oath."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.643,
                                "stop": 137.492,
                                "byte_start": 598259,
                                "byte_stop": 637651,
                                "text": "The panel held that the plain language of the statute foreclose the EEOC regulation allowing a later oath to relate back to an earlier charge."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 137.492,
                                "stop": 144.138,
                                "byte_start": 637651,
                                "byte_stop": 664192,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed today with the Clerk of the Court, we reversed the judgment of the Court of Appeals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 144.138,
                                "stop": 158.422,
                                "byte_start": 664192,
                                "byte_stop": 721348,
                                "text": "Section 706 of the Civil Rights Act requires a complainant to file what the Act calls a charge with EEOC within a certain time after the occurrences of an unlawful employment practice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 158.422,
                                "stop": 165.509,
                                "byte_start": 721348,
                                "byte_stop": 749664,
                                "text": "In a separate provision, the statute requires the complainant to affirm or swear that the allegations are true."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 165.509,
                                "stop": 173.376,
                                "byte_start": 749664,
                                "byte_stop": 781220,
                                "text": "Neither these two provisions defines what a charge is and the term is likewise undefined elsewhere in the statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.376,
                                "stop": 181.281,
                                "byte_start": 781220,
                                "byte_stop": 812776,
                                "text": "Neither provision incorporates the other so as to define charge by necessary implication as a charge under oath."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.281,
                                "stop": 185.072,
                                "byte_start": 812776,
                                "byte_stop": 827927,
                                "text": "The term charge is therefore open to interpretation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 185.072,
                                "stop": 197.561,
                                "byte_start": 827927,
                                "byte_stop": 877873,
                                "text": "We think that that EEOC regulation allowing a later oath to relate back to an earlier charge is consistent not only with the purposes of Title VII but also with background legal principles."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 197.561,
                                "stop": 214.396,
                                "byte_start": 877873,
                                "byte_stop": 945269,
                                "text": "Because we find the EEOC regulation to be not only a reasonable one but also the position we would adapt in the absence of any agency statement, we do not resolve any question of what deferences do to the agencies procedural rules."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 214.396,
                                "stop": 233.065,
                                "byte_start": 945269,
                                "byte_stop": 1019979,
                                "text": "In upholding the EEOC regulation we do not reach the conclusion drawn by the District Court and the single judge in the Court of Appeals, that quite apart from the oath issue, Edelman\u2019s November 1997 letter was not a charge under the statute because neither he nor the EEOC treated it as one."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 233.065,
                                "stop": 239.97,
                                "byte_start": 1019979,
                                "byte_stop": 1047565,
                                "text": "There is at least some support in the record for this view and we accordingly remand the case to the Court of Appeals to consider it."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 239.97,
                                "stop": 249.077,
                                "byte_start": 1047565,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed a concurring opinion and Justice O\u2019Connor has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment which Justice Scalia has joined."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
